<p>John and Dave are joined by TekRevue&#39;s Jim Tanous (aka MGGJim here at TMO). Jim&#39;s been managing his movie library digitally for years, and he talks through his workflow for ripping, storing, and playing back all this data; all while keeping it freed from any ecosystem lock-in (and future-proofing and other buzzwords, too). That plus your questions answered. Enjoy!</p>
